China Everbright Bank Co. was
ordered to raise its reserve ratio by 50 basis points on top of
another half percentage point increase for all lenders from Nov.
16 that was announced by the central bank, the 21st Century
Business Herald reported today, citing unidentified bank
officials.  The 50 basis points increase specifically for China
Everbright will be effective for three months, is on top of  on
Nov. 10, the newspaper reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
